ill, even if I believe little in the effect of meele stats except enough str to not be encumbered, sta over 100 so I do not have to cast estinguish fatigue and agi over 75 so you do not get the sharp AC drop.<br><br>Best recommendation I can make if you personally believe in agi increasing mob misses then work towards getting velious quest armour. That stuff will give you AC increase and return the stats you lost when you went with DW.<br><br>Pick your faction with what is realistic for you to obtain. It is painful, but later on you can switch factions. <br><br>For whatever reason I might parse some low and high AGI fights out just to get my personal confirmation of it. Might use a mob like a bulthor at the SG zone and after a 5-10 min test, zone out, change equipment and go back in to get beat on for another 5-10 min. People's environments they fight in and stats are always different, so verifying yourself at times is worth it, sometimes just to stop the inner fire that still wonders if you were right or wrong in the beginning. <br> <p>Senchy Solariatus60 Crusader of Rodcet Nife55 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)Dol Amroth<BR><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79641>My Profile</a><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udeebofoulmouth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>deebo foulmouth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/30/02 1:22:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Agility</span><hr size=1> again forgive my ignorance.. thanks for clearing that up. But beld becareful, some people read what you say as gold. I read your second reply and if I wasnt paying total attention I would have gone and tried to boost my agility to 175... Thanks everyone for the information.<br><br>I dont read the boards everyday, i couldnt i think i would lose my mind. As much as i want to be the ultimate paladin via equipment and stats, I dont find myself with some of the opportunities of some of the higher end guilds or whatnot. So I gather little bits of information here and there and just try to have fun with it.<br><br>Just hit 58 last night... looking for healing wave of prexus, dont really know if i will ever see it. Anyone know where it drops?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=334.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=334.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=334.topic&index=11><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.emailToFriend?topicID=334.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.threadControl?topicID=334.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=334.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=334.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of repli